\centering 
\includegraphics{03448.eps} 
\caption{\sl Silicon Solar cell } 
\label{03448.eps} 
\end{figure}

 

The ultimate commercial high efficiency (21.5\%) single crystal silicon solar cells have all contacts on the back of the  cell. The active area of the cell is increased by moving the top (-) contact conductors to the back of the cell. The top (-) contacts are normally made to the N-type silicon on top of the cell. In Figure~\ref{03452.eps} the (-) contacts are made to N$^{+}$ diffusions on the bottom interleaved with (+) contacts. The top surface is textured to aid in trapping light within the cell.. \cite{VSW}
 

 
