In Table~\ref{diodespice2.tbl}, we see that power rectifiers 1N3891 (12 A), and 10A04 (10 A) both use about 2. The first four in the table are not relevant because they are schottky, schottky, germanium, and silicon small signal, respectively. 
The saturation current, IS,  is derived from the diode equation, a value of (V$_{D}$, I$_{D}$) on the graph in Figure~\ref{03467.eps}, and N=2 (n in the diode equation). 
 

\bigskip 
\begingroup \vskip\parskip \everypar={\nobreak} \obeyspaces \frenchspacing \tt \obeylines \parskip=0pt \parindent=0pt 
