Like bipolar transistors, SCRs and TRIACs are also manufactured as light-sensitive devices, the action of impinging light replacing the function of triggering voltage.
 

 

Optically-controlled SCRs are often known by the acronym \textit{LASCR}, or \textbf{L}ight \textbf{A}ctivated \textbf{SCR}.  Its symbol, not surprisingly, looks like  Figure~\ref{03228.eps}.
 

 
